1
00:00:14,680 --> 00:00:16,320
Why is it a phone box?

2
00:00:17,480 --> 00:00:18,600
Sorry, what?

3
00:00:19,240 --> 00:00:20,880
On the outside, it said "Police Box".

4
00:00:20,960 --> 00:00:23,160
Why have you labelled
a time machine "Police Box"?

5
00:00:23,240 --> 00:00:24,960
Why not "Time Machine"?
Is that too obvious?

6
00:00:25,040 --> 00:00:26,880
And what is a police box?
Do policemen come in boxes?

7
00:00:26,960 --> 00:00:28,520
How many do you get?
Are you a policeman?

8
00:00:28,600 --> 00:00:31,920
No. Look at your hair.
Actually, just look at your hair!

9
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:36,880
Do you ever look at your hair and think,
"Whoa! It just won't stop! And my chin!

10
00:00:36,960 --> 00:00:39,720
"Look, I'm wearing a bow tie.
Shoot me now!"

11
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:41,920
-Am I gabbling?
-A bit, yeah.

12
00:00:42,640 --> 00:00:43,720
-The question stands.
-The first question?

13
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:45,400
-Yes.
-Well, it's not really a police box,

14
00:00:45,480 --> 00:00:47,360
which by the way,
is a special kind of telephone box

15
00:00:47,440 --> 00:00:48,680
that policemen used to use.

16
00:00:48,760 --> 00:00:51,320
Right. Telephone box.
There's a light on the top.

17
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:52,600
Don't you need to change the bulb?

18
00:00:52,680 --> 00:00:53,880
Amy, stop. Breath.

19
00:00:53,960 --> 00:00:54,960
(EXHALES)

20
00:00:55,040 --> 00:00:57,000
-(INHALES DEEPLY)
-Hmm?

21
00:00:57,760 --> 00:01:00,320
Why doesn't the air get out?
It is made of wood.

22
00:01:00,400 --> 00:01:03,320
Oh, you've got a wooden time machine.
Do you feel stupid?

23
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:05,800
-Sorry. Back on the bow tie.
-It's camouflage.

24
00:01:05,880 --> 00:01:08,800
It's disguised as a police telephone box
from 1963.

25
00:01:08,880 --> 00:01:11,160
Every time the Tardis materialises
in a new location,

26
00:01:11,240 --> 00:01:14,960
within the first nanosecond of landing,
it analyses its surroundings,

27
00:01:15,040 --> 00:01:18,200
calculates a 12-dimensional data map
of everything within a 1000-mile radius,

28
00:01:18,280 --> 00:01:22,360
and determines which outer shell would
blend in best with the environment.

29
00:01:23,040 --> 00:01:26,760
And then it disguises itself
as a police telephone box from 1963.

30
00:01:27,720 --> 00:01:28,880
Oh. Why?

31
00:01:28,960 --> 00:01:32,600
It's probably a bit of a fault,
actually. I've been meaning to check.

32
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:34,240
What, it's a police box every time?

33
00:01:34,320 --> 00:01:36,280
Yeah. I suppose, now you mention.

34
00:01:36,360 --> 00:01:38,080
How long has it been doing that?

35
00:01:38,160 --> 00:01:40,040
Oh! You know, not long.

36
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:42,440
Okay. Okay, but what about the windows?

37
00:01:42,520 --> 00:01:46,160
There are windows on the outside.
Where do they go? Is it a cry for help?

38
00:01:46,240 --> 00:01:47,680
-What?
-The bow tie.

39
00:01:47,760 --> 00:01:48,960
Ah.

40
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:50,920
Bow ties are cool.

41
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:53,120
-And you're an alien.
-Yeah.

42
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:56,320
Well, in your terms, yeah.
In my terms, you're an alien.

43
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:59,040
-In quite a few people's terms probably.
-What kind of alien?

44
00:01:59,120 --> 00:02:01,720
Well, you know, a nice one.
Definitely one of the nice ones.

45
00:02:01,800 --> 00:02:04,800
So you're like a space squid
or something?

46
00:02:05,440 --> 00:02:08,400
Are you like a tiny little slug
in @ human suit?

47
00:02:08,480 --> 00:02:09,880
Is that why you walk like that?

48
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:14,040
Amy, this is me.
This is what I really look like.

49
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:16,840
-Well, that's fine, then!
-Ow! Good!

50
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:21,080
Okay. I think I'm done there.

51
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:22,880
(BOTH LAUGHING)

52
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:24,280
Amy Pond,

53
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:27,840
you've barely started.

54
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:33,320
Plus, do you know what I keep in here?

55
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:35,640
What?

56
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:40,040
Absolutely everything.

57
00:02:44,640 --> 00:02:46,640
Anything take your fancy?

58
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:53,200
-We're in space.
-Yeah. That's space.

59
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:54,360
-But it can't be.
-But it is.

60
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:57,280
It's like, it's like, it's like...
special effects.

61
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:59,720
-Like what?
-This so isn't real. It's not real.

62
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:02,480
-Get out.
-What?

63
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:04,520
Yeah. Seriously. Get out!

64
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:06,080
(AMY SCREAMS)

